ding="|||" custom_padding_last_edited="off|desktop" animation_style="slide" animation_direction="left" animation_intensity_slide="2%" locked="off"]<h5>established since 2004</h5><h1>Heaven\'s Nest</h1><h1>cHILD cARE</h1><h6><span style="color: #dd6700;">Child Care &amp; Recreation Centre</span></h6>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_5" _builder_version="3.14" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" disabled_on="off|off|on" _builder_version="3.14" background_color="#efe9e4" custom_padding="0|0px|0|0px|false|false"][et_pb_row custom_padding="0|0px|27px|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.14"][et_pb_column type="4_4" _builder_version="3.14" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_divider _builder_version="3.14"][/et_pb_divider][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" admin_label="Services" _builder_version="3.14" background_color="#efe9e4" background_color_gradient_direction="90deg" background_size="initial" background_position="top_left" background_repeat="repeat" custom_padding="29px|0px|60px|0px|false|false"][et_pb_row custom_padding="0|0px|0|0px|false|false" _builder_version="3.7" module_alignment="center"][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.0.47" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.7" text_font="||||||||" text_font_size="16px" text_line_height="2em" header_font="||||||||" header_2_font="Oswald|||on|||||" header_2_line_height="1.5em" header_4_font="||||||||" custom_margin="|||" locked="off"]<h2>Heaven\'s Nest Child Care Centre</h2>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.14" text_font="||||||||" text_font_size="16px" text_line_height="2em" header_font="||||||||" header_4_font="Oswald|||on|||||" header_4_font_size="30px" header_4_line_height="1.5em" header_6_font="Roboto|700||on|||||" header_6_text_color="#d9907d" header_6_font_size="16px" header_6_letter_spacing="1px" header_6_line_height="1.8em" custom_margin="|||" custom_margin_tablet="|||" custom_margin_phone="|||" custom_margin_last_edited="on|desktop"]<h6><span style="color: #dd6700;">HEAVEN\'S nEST: HOLISTIC FOSTER CARE TO INCLUDE EDUCATION</span></h6><p>On the 18<sup>th</sup> of September local children’s home, Heaven’s Nest will officially launch their newly built classroom.  Heaven’s Nest is an emergency foster home for children under the age of 8 that have been abused, abandoned, neglected or are affected by HIV &amp; AIDS. “Many of the children that we take in have had no exposure to even basic education. This means that when they were sent to school in the past, they were often unprepared for it,” says Eleanor Bester, the coordinator at Heaven’s Nest.</p><p>Heaven’s Nest aims to provide holistic care for children in need. Bester spotted the need for a classroom on their property to add to the loving, safe home, healthy food, medical care, counselling and play therapy already provided.</p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.14" text_font="||||||||" text_font_size="16px" text_line_height="2em" header_font="||||||||" header_4_font="Oswald|||on|||||" header_4_font_size="30px" header_4_line_height="1.5em" header_6_font="Roboto|700||on|||||" header_6_text_color="#d9907d" header_6_font_size="16px" header_6_letter_spacing="1px" header_6_line_height="1.8em" custom_margin="|||" custom_margin_tablet="|||" custom_margin_phone="|||" custom_margin_last_edited="on|desktop"]<h6><span style="color: #dd6700;">A STEP TOWARS SELF-SUSTAINABILITY</span></h6><p>Emergency foster care home, Heaven’s Nest, has taken another step towards self-sustainability with the help of SPAR Distribution Centre in Philippi, who commissioned a vegetable garden on the property.</p><p>“The aim of the project is two-fold,” says Heaven’s Nest co-ordinator Eleanor Bester. “The vegetables can be harvested every six weeks, which allows us to provide fresh organic seasonal vegetables for the children, and what we don’t use can be sold, allowing us to provide other food, clothing and necessities.”</p><p>Heaven’s Nest is currently providing care to 12 children between three and seven years old. These numbers change constantly, since they do not institutionalise children, but rather care for them when they are in a state of need, until they can be re-integrated into their families or placed in foster care.</p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="3.0.47" parallax="off" parallax_method="on"][et_pb_image src="https://site-export-ktich.c9users.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/db920fee-img_2114.jpg" _builder_version="3.14"][/et_pb_image][et_pb_image src="https://site-export-ktich.c9users.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/6715f2a9-img_2107.jpg" _builder_version="3.14" custom_margin="-30px|||"][/et_pb_image][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.14" text_font="||||||||" text_font_size="16px" text_line_height="2em" header_font="||||||||" header_4_font="Oswald|||on|||||" header_4_font_size="30px" header_4_line_height="1.5em" header_6_font="Roboto|700||on|||||" header_6_text_color="#d9907d" header_6_font_size="16px" header_6_letter_spacing="1px" header_6_line_height="1.8em" custom_margin="|||" custom_margin_tablet="|||" custom_margin_phone="|||" custom_margin_last_edited="on|desktop"]<h6><span style="color: #dd6700;">where do your donation go?</span></h6>\n<p>Giving back to your community is a noble thought and there are many worthy causes out there. But what do those causes actually do with your donations? Local Cape Town emergency foster home Heaven’s Nest made fishes from loaves in 2011 despite a sharp decrease in donations.</p>\n<p>“They visited and gave donations in kind, including clothing, toys, non-perishable foods and even cooked suppers and lunches. With their help, we provided a safe and loving home to 42 children in 2011 and have made some wonderful changes to the establishment too,” says Bester.</p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" _buil